				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Greetings.
<br />

<br />
I just wanted to mention this: transparency effects which work in vanilla Q2 with OpenGL don't work in KmQuake2 anymore. 
<br />

<br />
This is bad, because some of the most beautiful and experimental newschool/gothic maps for Q2 use such effects, like Musashi'S Broken Shadows, amongst many others.
<br />

<br />
Talking as a mapper/map lover/map collector here.
<br />
KmQuake2 is most likely the best Q2 sourceport there is, but this issue prevents me from using it more.
<br />

<br />
Making KmQuake2 compatible with these special effects would be a serious improvement.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<img src="http://img216.imageshack.us/img216/8959/kmquake2005wq6.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
<img src="http://img300.imageshack.us/img300/8969/kmquake2006hu9.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
<img src="http://img300.imageshack.us/img300/24/kmquake2007dr9.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class=sign><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.aon.at/sublevel404/images/misc/clanq2clogogrieve0qt.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

