			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Try turning off transparent lighting and glass envmaps in the advanced video menu.  This problem can be prevented entirely by setting the 0x01000000 flag on such surfaces, see the screenshot linked below:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.markshan.com/knightmare/pics/qer147_nolightmapflag.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.markshan.com/knightmare/pics/qer147_nolightmapflag.jpg</a>
<br />

<br />
BTW, here's a pic of some of the new effects supported in the next version of KMQuake2:
<br />
<a href="http://www.markshan.com/knightmare/pics/kmq2_glows1.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.markshan.com/knightmare/pics/kmq2_glows1.jpg</a></span><span class=sign></span><span class="gensmall"></span>
