				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No, it's the flag next to hint.
<br />

<br />
The glow effect is created by making a texture called &lt;texturename&gt;_glow of the same dimensions.  There won't be any Q3 shaders or rscript in the upcoming version, though there will be a limited scripting system for models.
<br />

<br />
I've been looking at Q2E's shader system, but it doesn't support transparent entities or bmodels.  It uses a REALLY dirty hack for rendering specific transparent models, referring to specific filenames.  And any model or bmodel can become transparent at any time in KMQ2, so it looks like I'll have to write my own system or re-write Q2E's.</span><span class=sign></span><span class="gensmall"></span>
                  <br /><br />
                  </td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
